The study further shows that HIV infection rates among young girls between the ages of 19 and 24 years old still remains the highest. The studies were presented to the more than 3000 delegates attending the four-day 9th AIDS Conference in Durban. 

The conference was officially opened by Health Minister Dr. Zweli Mkhize. 

